00:14:55.170 --> 00:15:30.310
you want to treat things differently. Okay.
Let's pop back to... Okay. So let's talk about

00:15:30.310 --> 00:15:43.740
money. Now, obviously, you know, that's--this
is the big question, you know, how do we make

00:15:43.740 --> 00:15:52.470
money with web apps? As you know more people
are spending more of their time online everyday.

00:15:52.470 --> 00:15:58.970
The Web continues to grow. This continues
to be the best reach of any platform out there

00:15:58.970 --> 00:16:05.839
and it's only getting better. But, again,
as you k now, monetizing web apps is not always

00:16:05.839 --> 00:16:12.300
easy. Now, probably, the easiest way today
is to use advertising, and advertising has

00:16:12.300 --> 00:16:18.750
been great. It's really easy to set up, you
know, you just sign up for your account, drop

00:16:18.750 --> 00:16:25.149
in a little JavaScript on your page and, you
know, start getting checks. It's pretty easy

00:16:25.149 --> 00:16:31.860
on that front. But it may not work for everybody
and for all cases and so we want to provide

00:16:31.860 --> 00:16:39.800
other options. So, for example, it really
works best when you have a lot of traffic,

00:16:39.800 --> 00:16:45.510
you know, adds some volume. Advertising is
about volume. It's also has, you know, about,

00:16:45.510 --> 00:16:49.860
you know, having low fixed costs to run your
site. That's sort of the ideal case, a small

00:16:49.860 --> 00:16:55.140
shop with a lot of traffic. If you would say
a large new organization with a lot of foreign

00:16:55.140 --> 00:17:01.920
bureaus, that's a huge fixed cost to overcome.
If you're a small company, you know, getting

00:17:01.920 --> 00:17:07.819
enough traffic to even pay for your small
number of employees is a big hurdle to overcome

00:17:07.819 --> 00:17:13.260
to attract users. You might have a lot of
marketing cost to overcome. And if for whatever

00:17:13.260 --> 00:17:17.909
reason, you're costs are high or your traffic
is low, you don't actually get to set the

00:17:17.909 --> 00:17:23.659
price. It is what it is. So, you can't tweak
the knobs and say, "Oh, I need to charge more

00:17:23.659 --> 00:17:29.799
because--in order to make my business work,"
so in order to do that you really have to

00:17:29.799 --> 00:17:39.690
charge for it. So let's look at what it takes
to actually sell your web app today. Okay.

00:17:39.690 --> 00:17:45.460
So you can sell it but there've been a lot
of barriers to getting there. First of, it's

00:17:45.460 --> 00:17:50.179
actually pretty--it's a lot of work. You have
to integrate with payment processors, choose

00:17:50.179 --> 00:17:53.960
which one, choose which, you know, credit
cards you're going to accept and figure out

00:17:53.960 --> 00:17:57.739
all the legal arrangement you needed to make
to take that, deal with a lot of issues of

00:17:57.739 --> 00:18:01.899
like chargebacks and taxes if you need to
go international and most of you will because,

00:18:01.899 --> 00:18:08.070
you know, the Web is global. International
is a whole another bowl of wax. You need to

00:18:08.070 --> 00:18:12.980
have bank accounts in all the different countries
and deal with, again, all the local regulations

00:18:12.980 --> 00:18:18.340
and rules. Now, you combine some of those,
some of that pain, some of those difficulties

00:18:18.340 --> 00:18:23.200
with the problems I was talking about before,
you know, where there's a lot of buying friction

00:18:23.200 --> 00:18:28.509
for users and the users can't find you to
begin with and don't even know you exist.

00:18:28.509 --> 00:18:32.909
You're user acquisition cost wind up being
pretty high. You know, you have to, you know,

00:18:32.909 --> 00:18:38.370
do big marketing campaigns to drop people
there. And because every user accounts and

00:18:38.370 --> 00:18:45.049
you're, you know, trying to make it all work,
you--the common decision that's made is to

00:18:45.049 --> 00:18:49.039
try to be as broad as you can in terms of
which browser you're going to support and

00:18:49.039 --> 00:18:52.990
which features you're going to support. That
means that you've aimed for the least capable

00:18:52.990 --> 00:18:59.350
browser. You don't take advantage of all the
rich features of the Web because that's, you

00:18:59.350 --> 00:19:04.840
know, you need to reach as many users as you
can. We believe the Web Store can help cut

00:19:04.840 --> 00:19:11.179
through a lot of these issues. So first of,
we're here to try to do as much of heavy lifting

00:19:11.179 --> 00:19:16.649
as we can. We want to make the transaction
process as simple as we can and we want to

00:19:16.649 --> 00:19:21.779
handle the licensing and make that really
trivial. And the thing about this is that

00:19:21.779 --> 00:19:27.489
the Web is not a closed ecosystem. We're not--we
don't have a captive where you have no choice

00:19:27.489 --> 00:19:33.169
but to go through us. As I said, you can sell
in the Web today. There are other options.

00:19:33.169 --> 00:19:37.621
So we're competing against what else is out
there, so we've got to be good. We've got

00:19:37.621 --> 00:19:47.779
to compete against that and make things smoother
for people. So how do you do this? Well, as

00:19:47.779 --> 00:19:53.509
we've talked about, web apps are really, you
know, you know what they are. You build them

00:19:53.509 --> 00:19:59.470
exactly as normal. Once you've got your app,
we're ready to go. You then come and sign

00:19:59.470 --> 00:20:04.269
up for an account with the Web Store, you
know, just get your bank account set up, get,

00:20:04.269 --> 00:20:10.059
